(169, 'Bottle Rocket IPA', 3, 31, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'An explosion of hops dominate this deep golden ale. Brewed with four varieties of hops & dry hopped with three other hops, the flavor is powerful. Not a harsh bitterness, but a full hop flavor.'),
(170, 'Wicked Ale', 3, 38, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Pete\'s Wicked Ale is an experience out of the ordinary. Our tantalizing ruby-brown ale with distinctive malts and aromatic Brewers Gold hops is sure to stir up an urge to get loose.'),
(171, 'Red MacGregor', 1, 15, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Red Macgregor is a unique beer: delicate and sophisticated yet the robust cask conditioned version of this beer was the first Scottish beer to win the BIIA World Cask Beer Gold Medal.On the nose this ruby-red beer is delicate this ruby-red beer is delicateOn the nose this ruby-red beer is delicate floral and fruity floral and fruityOn the nose this ruby-red beer is delicate floral and fruity with notes of violets with notes of violetsOn the nose this ruby-red beer is delicate floral and fruity with notes of violets cherries cherriesOn the nose this ruby-red beer is delicate floral and fruity with notes of violets cherries toffee and caramel.  toffee and caramel. On the palate the fruits combine with a juicy malt character and hints of toasted malt the fruits combine with a juicy malt character and hints of toasted maltOn the palate the fruits combine with a juicy malt character and hints of toasted malt with a biscuit malt and spicy hop finish.\" with a biscuit malt and spicy hop finish.\"On the palate the fruits combine with a juicy malt character and hints of toasted malt with a biscuit malt and spicy hop finish.\"'),
(172, 'Rugged Trail Ale', 3, 38, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Designed as our session beer, Rugged Trail Nut Brown Ale is bronze in color with a velvety smooth taste and subtle chocolate note. Rugged Trailâ€™s lower alcohol content and subtle hoppiness make it the perfect beer to enjoy during the day and into the night.'),
(173, 'Big Bark Amber Lager', 8, 95, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', '\\Smooth\\\" is the first word from your mouth after a taste of Big Bark Amber. This Vienna-style lager has a reddish-amber color with a smooth'),
(174, 'High Seas IPA', 3, 31, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Our interpretation of a legendary style ale is not for the timid. Assertively hoppy and dangerously seductive. A skillful blend of three premium barley malts with generous amounts of Northern Brewer and Cascade Hops creates a special ale to satisfy even the most demanding palate.'),
(175, 'Point Defiance IPA', 3, 31, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Four types of malted barley, including a specially roasted Belgium barley make up the grain bill. Centennial, Sterling, and Amarillo hops provide the big hoppy flavor. Double dry-hopped, once with raw Centennial hops and once with raw Amarillo hops present this beer\'s huge hop aroma.'),
(176, 'Big Eye IPA', 3, 31, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'ndia Pale Ale is a style of beer that was developed in England during the period of the British Empire. It is derived from bitter ales but contains even more alcohol and hops. This helped preserve the beer on its long sea journey around Cape Hope to India.British troops returning from India brought their love of this beer back with them so breweries began brewing it for the home market as well. Sadly the style had mostly died out in England by the late twentieth century. the style had mostly died out in England by the late twentieth century.2449Colorado Belle DarkColorado Belle Dark'),
(177, 'Gubna Imperial IPA', 3, 32, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Emphasizing that complexity of character can arise from simple elements, this ale is made with three malts and one hop. Its light amber color and slightly spicy malt character are derived from the use of German Dark Munich Malt and Rye Malt respectively. North American 2-row barley combines with the other grains to lay the foundation for the hop onslaught to come. Summit hops are used exclusively in the boil for bitterness, flavor and aroma but it doesnâ€™t end there. Post-fermentation dry hopping allows the 9.5% ABV monstrosity to gently coax the citrus rind and grapefruit aroma to join the 100 IBUs already present. This beer should greet you with a pungent citrus blast, provide a spicy yet round middle and finish with a brisk, clean bitterness.'),
