(191, 'Jack Whacker Wheat Ale', 11, 116, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Jack Whacker Wheat Ale is a light, unfiltered brew with a citrus aroma and flavor imparted by a late addition of lemon grass. It\'s the perfect refreshment for a thirsty, trail-weary ale lover.'),
(192, 'Shiner Kosmos Reserve', 8, 95, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Kosmos Spoetzl knew how to brew great beer. Born in Bavaria, Kosmosâ€™ mastery of German brewing carried him as far as Egypt before he found his way to the small Texas town of Shiner. Our proud brewery still carries his name and commitment to excellence in brewing. This full-flavored, hop-jacked lager is every bit as unique as the man himself and our way of saluting the brewmaster who started it all.'),
(193, 'Saint Arnold Brown Ale', 3, 38, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'A beautiful, deep copper brown ale. It has a full, malty body with hints of chocolate, a touch of sweetness and a light hop flavor. A complex malt character is created by combining five different types of malts. It has a rich, creamy head with a fine lace. The light fruitiness, characteristic of ales, is derived from a proprietary yeast strain. Saint Arnold Brown Ale is best consumed at 45-50Â° Fahrenheit.\"3107Rainbow Red AleRainbow Red Ale'),
(194, 'Skullsplitter Ale', 1, 15, '9', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Skull Splitter is our strongest ale: which is named after Thorfinn Einarsson who was the 7th Viking Earl of Orkney. Sophisticated, satiny smooth with a deceptively light character, it is a tribute to our colourful forbear.On the nose this strong beer has a fruity malt character this strong beer has a fruity malt characterOn the nose this strong beer has a fruity malt character with hints of dark fruit with hints of dark fruitOn the nose this strong beer has a fruity malt character with hints of dark fruit spicy hop spicy hopOn the nose this strong beer has a fruity malt character with hints of dark fruit spicy hop dates and figs. dates and figs.On the palate rich and complex with sweet toasted malt rich and complex with sweet toasted maltOn the palate rich and complex with sweet toasted malt molasses molassesOn the palate rich and complex with sweet toasted malt molasses fresh and dried fruit and hints of warming spices.\" fresh and dried fruit and hints of warming spices.\"On the palate rich and complex with sweet toasted malt molasses fresh and dried fruit and hints of warming spices.\"'),
(195, 'Sly Fox Christmas Ale', 11, 141, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'This malty, full-bodied red ale is made with traditional mulling spices: Ginger, Clove, All Spice, Cinnamon & Nutmeg. If this one doesn\'t get you into the Christmas spirit, you truly are a Scrooge.'),
(196, 'Jubelale', 11, 141, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Did you know that Jubelale was the first beer ever bottled by Deschutes Brewery?  Highly anticipated every fall, Jubelale is in a category of its own with a flavor and following that is impossible to match.  Dark crystal malt creates that â€œlusciousâ€ holiday note while the roasty flavor and bountiful hops excite your tastebuds, reminding you why Jubelale is the perfect holiday beer'),
(197, 'Cross of Gold', 3, 37, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'An american blonde ale with bursts of fruity aroma and a dry finish.'),
(198, 'Harvest Ale', 3, 26, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'The cornerstone of our Harvest series is the beer that started the modern-day fresh hop ale phenomenon in America, our original Harvest Ale. Created in 1996 Harvest Ale features Cascade and Centennial hops from the Yakima Valley in Eastern Washington. These hops are harvested and shipped as â€œwetâ€ un-dried hopsâ€”the same day they are pickedâ€”to our brewery in Chico where our brewers eagerly wait to get them into the brew kettle while their oils and resins are still at their peak.\" Harvest Ale features Cascade and Centennial hops from the Yakima Valley in Eastern Washington. These hops are harvested and shipped as â€œwetâ€ un-dried hopsâ€”the same day they are pickedâ€”to our brewery in Chico where our brewers eagerly wait to get them into the brew kettle while their oils and resins are still at their peak.\"Created in 1996 Harvest Ale features Cascade and Centennial hops from the Yakima Valley in Eastern Washington. These hops are harvested and shipped as â€œwetâ€ un-dried hopsâ€”the same day they are pickedâ€”to our brewery in Chico where our brewers eagerly wait to get them into the brew kettle while their oils and resins are still at their peak.\"'),
(199, 'Road Dog Ale', 2, 25, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Blessed by Hunter S. Thompson... Road Dog Porter was our first beer to be illustrated by Ralph Steadman. This is a dark, rich and malty beer, with hints of chocolate and licorice resulting from the use of four prized malts.'),
(200, 'Hoppy Claus Holiday Ale', 11, 141, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Our Holiday Ale is a â€œspecialâ€ version of our flagship product - Hoppy Faceâ„¢ Amber Ale'),
(201, 'Total Eclipse Black Ale', 3, 42, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Total Eclipse Black Ale has been described as similar to a light, dry stout. Characterized by its distinctive hop aroma and rich, black color, Total Eclipse redefines the way you think about a dark ale. Brewed at a low temperature to create a refreshingly dry finish, Total Eclipse uses only the finest two row malted barley and hops grown in the great Pacific Northwest. This combination results in a clean, crisp, hand-crafted experience. Hoppy Brewing Company has never used any artificial preservatives, flavors, or colors in any of its ales. The Hoppy label is your guarantee of purity. Itâ€™s â€œtotallyâ€ out of this world delicious!!!\"3462Rosed PorterRosed Porter'),
(202, 'Saranac Winter Wassail', 11, 141, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'At the heart of Saranac Winter Wassail is a classic English ale brewed with English Malt & Fuggles Hops. Look for hits of cinnamon, nutmeg, orange and allspice. Cheers to the holiday season!'),
(203, 'Liquid Sunshine Blonde Ale', 3, 37, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 's a unique, all-natural style of beer that currently falls under the category of a Specialty Ale. In other words, there is no true category for this beer... Characterized by its distinctive Mount Hood hop aroma and beautiful blonde color, Liquid Sunshineâ„¢ is brewed at a low temperature to create a nice light dry finish. Using only the finest 2-row malted barley, wheat, rye, and great northwestern grown hops, this combination results in a clean, crisp, and uniquely refreshing beer. As usual, no artificial preservatives have been added to our beer during and/or after the brewing process...Thereâ€™s nothing like it under the sun!!!\"3481High Rollers Wheat BeerHigh Rollers Wheat Beer'),
(204, 'Hoppy Face Amber Ale', 3, 31, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Is an award-winning, traditional, all-natural style of beer that falls under the category of a \\West Coast\\\" India Pale Ale (IPA). Characterized by its high hop contentIt will put a smile on your face!!!\"\"\"'),
(205, 'Brown Ale', 3, 38, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'A mix of Northern and Southern English Brown Ales, blending 6 malts into an All-American beer.'),
(206, 'Base Camp Golden Ale', 3, 37, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'The lightest of FiftyFifty\'s ales, Base Camp is a thirst quenching delight. Pale straw to light gold in color, this beer has a mild malt flavor combined with light bitterness and hop flavor. This beer finishes dry and is very light and refreshing on the palate. Base Camp is a \\session beer\\\"'),
(207, 'Affligem Dubbel', 5, 60, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'A reddish-brown abbey ale brewed with dark malts. The secondary fermentation gives a fruity aroma and a unique, spicy character with a distinctive aftertaste. Secondary fermentation in the bottle. Contains barley malt.'),
(208, 'Mirrorpond Pale Ale', 3, 26, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Mirror Pond is just a short walk from the Deschutes Brewery & Public House in downtown Bend and reflects the Three Sisters Mountains. This scenic spot alongside the Deschutes River is the localsâ€™ choice for summer festivals and concerts.'),
(209, 'Samuel Adams Cranberry Lambic', 5, 70, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Samuel Adams Cranberry Lambic is a fruit beer that draws its flavor not just from the cranberries it is brewed with, but also from the unique fermentation character imparted by the rare wild yeast strain. The result is a flavor rich in fruitiness and reminiscent of cranberries and bananas, cloves and nutmeg. The yeast fermentation also will create a slight sourness on the sides of the palate, a signature of the original Lambic style which, with the subtle cereal note from the wheat malt, remind its drinker that, as fruity a beer as this is, it is still a beer.'),
(210, 'Snow Cap', 1, 13, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'A rich, full-bodied winter warmer crafted in the British tradition of holiday beers. This deep mahogany colored brew balances complex fruit flavors with a refreshingly smooth texture, making Snow Cap a highly drinkable and desirable cold weather companion.'),
(211, 'Obsidian Stout', 3, 42, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Obsidian Stout gets is inspiration from one of the world\'s largest obsidian flows at Newberry Volcano--just a few miles south of the brewery.  \\The Big Obsidian Flow'),
