(329, 'Imperial Pumpkin Ale', 11, 123, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Yes that\'s right!  The mother of all Pumpkin Ales is currently in transit to our wholesalers and should be out on shelves around mid-September.  This 8.0% ABV pumpkin ale is heartier, spicier, and more \\caramelly\\\" and \\\"pumpkiny\\\" than its faint brethren!    Perfect finisher on a cool autumn night\" then you just don\'t like mothers!\" then you just don\'t like mothers!\"  Perfect finisher on a cool autumn night\" then you just don\'t like mothers!\"393511,111.1  Insanity is 11.1% ABV. It is best enjoyed in a brandy snifter and served at 45-50 degrees F.\"3936Muse Farmhouse AleMuse Farmhouse Ale3936Muse Farmhouse Ale6.26.2Old Heathen imperial stout is our interpretation of a beer style that originated in the 18th century. Brewed in England and exported to Germany Scandinavia and Russia Scandinavia and RussiaOld Heathen imperial stout is our interpretation of a beer style that originated in the 18th century. Brewed in England and exported to Germany Scandinavia and Russia these beers became fashionable among the members of the Czar\'s court. In order to survive long voyages they were brewed with high alcohol content to prevent spoilage. And at 8.0% ABV (alcohol by volume) Old Heathen definitely contains a warming belt. You may want to lay down a few bottles for future evaluation- this beer keeps well and will only get better with age. these beers became fashionable among the members of the Czar\'s court. In order to survive long voyages they were brewed with high alcohol content to prevent spoilage. And at 8.0% ABV (alcohol by volume) Old Heathen definitely contains a warming belt. You may want to lay down a few bottles for future evaluation- this beer keeps well and will only get better with age.'),
