(539, 'Stovepipe Porter', 2, 25, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Stovepipe Porter is made in the traditional porter stlye, and is a favorite with all porter lovers. Ruby-black in color, Stovepipe Porter has a rich palate and a roasted, hoppy aroma. It is delicious on its own or with a meal, and tastes great with chocolate.'),
(540, 'White Sail', 5, 67, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'White Sail is a Belgian-style white beer, craft brewed with wheat, malted barley, hops, and a little bit of coriander and orange peel. It is mild yet flavorful, with fruity undertones and a haze from the yeast and wheat. This ale is delicious on its own, or with a slice of orange.'),
(541, 'Vermont Lager', 8, 95, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A classic European style lager. We take the time to brew this beer as a true lager should be brewed. And it\'s well worth the wait! You can enjoy the drinkability of this light-gold, refreshing beer with friends at the pub or at home after a long day.'),
(542, 'Long Trail Ale', 4, 57, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Long Trail Ale is a full-bodied amber ale modeled after the \\Alt-biers\\\" of DÃ¼sseldorf'),
(543, 'Traditional IPA', 3, 31, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'The first IPAs were unfiltered and featured extra hops and higher strength as a preservative for the long trip from England to the colony of India. Our Traditional IPA is naturally carbonated, dry-hopped & unfiltered like the old days.'),
(544, 'Double Bag Ale', 5, 60, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'This malty, full-bodied double alt is also know as \\Stickebier\\\" - German slang for \\\"secret brew\\\". Double Bag was originally offered only in our brewery taproom as a special treat to our visitors.\"'),
(545, 'Long Trail Hefeweizen', 4, 50, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Here is our \\Wheat Beer with Yeast\\\"'),
(546, 'Harvest', 3, 38, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'A light & malty experience modeled after one of our favorite old style English brews.'),
(547, 'Hibernator', 1, 15, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'This robust and malty brew will take the bite from a cold winter night.'),
(548, 'Blackbeary Wheat', 11, 116, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Light & refreshing with a hint of blackberry at the finish makes this beer a real thirst quencher. For the health conscious, Blackbeary Wheat has less than 6 grams of carbs and contains 0 fat.'),
(549, 'Steamwhistle Lager', 8, 95, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Good clean lager.'),
(550, 'Belgian White', 5, 67, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Our Belgian White Ale is modeled after the original Belgian Witbiers brewed in monasteries during the early 14th century. The soft notes of citrus and spice are topped with a light, fluffy head that finishes clean and crisp. This all natural ale is our latest seasonal brew, perfect for lounging lake-side or celebrating at trail\'s end.'),
(551, 'La Fin Du Monde', 5, 61, '9', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'La Fin du Monde has a brilliant golden color with vigorously effervescent foam.It is midly yeasty with a complex palate of malt fruit and spice notes followed by a smooth fruit and spice notes followed by a smoothIt is midly yeasty with a complex palate of malt fruit and spice notes followed by a smooth dry finish.\" dry finish.\"It is midly yeasty with a complex palate of malt fruit and spice notes followed by a smooth dry finish.\"43623,853.85'),
(552, 'Commodore Perry IPA', 3, 31, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'A medium-bodied and well hopped India Pale Ale with a dry, fruity aftertaste.'),
(553, 'Eliot Ness Amber Lager', 8, 95, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'An amber lager with rich, fragrant malt flavors balanced by crisp, noble hops.'),
(554, 'Burning River Pale Ale', 3, 26, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'An assertively hopped American Pale Ale with citrusy and piney Cascade hops.'),
(555, 'Holy Moses', 5, 72, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'A Belgian Wit Ale spiced with orange peel, chamomile and coriander.'),
(556, 'Ohio City Oatmeal Stout', 3, 42, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A smooth and creamy medium-bodied stout with soft malty notes and dry finish.'),
(557, 'Negra Modelo', 8, 95, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Negra Modelo has long been the dark beer alternative for Mexican beer drinkers. It has been identified as one of the few surviving examples of Vienna style lager - a style that was largely replaced in European breweries with Oktoberfest, a slightly lighter lager, in the early twentieth century. Negra Modelo pours with an off-white medium head. The body is clear with a rich amber/copper color. The aroma is sweet with hints of apple. The impression at the first sip is sweet. This gives way only a bit to some hops bitterness which gives some balance but leaves the beer firmly in the sweet category. It has no real lager snap at the end medium head. The body is clear with a rich amber/copper color. The aroma is sweet with hints of apple. The impression at the first sip is sweet. This gives way only a bit to some hops bitterness which gives some balance but leaves the beer firmly in the sweet category. It has no real lager snap at the endNegra Modelo pours with an off-white medium head. The body is clear with a rich amber/copper color. The aroma is sweet with hints of apple. The impression at the first sip is sweet. This gives way only a bit to some hops bitterness which gives some balance but leaves the beer firmly in the sweet category. It has no real lager snap at the end just lingering hops. This actually makes the second sip more balanced than the first. just lingering hops. This actually makes the second sip more balanced than the first.There is some complexity and depth here but the flavors are very delicate. They are obliterated by the aggressive flavors of the Mexican food that Modelo is often served with making it a sweet balance to the savory and sometimes hot cuisine.\"4372Birra Moretti La RossaBirra Moretti La Rossa4372Birra Moretti La Rossa7.27.2'),
(558, 'Lone Star', 8, 95, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'The National Beer of Texas\\Lone Star beer uses the finest hops from the Pacific Northwest with hearty grains from the Central and Northern Plains. The GABF recognized Lone Star as a high quality American Cream Lager by awarding it with a silver medal. Malted barley and corn extract combine to provide Lone Star with nature\'s finest ingredients for brewing. Lone Star\'s ingredients give this beer its full natural flavor. The choicest hops lend complexity and aroma to this beer\" body body\\Lone Star beer uses the finest hops from the Pacific Northwest with hearty grains from the Central and Northern Plains. The GABF recognized Lone Star as a high quality American Cream Lager by awarding it with a silver medal. Malted barley and corn extract combine to provide Lone Star with nature\'s finest ingredients for brewing. Lone Star\'s ingredients give this beer its full natural flavor. The choicest hops lend complexity and aroma to this beer\" body and character.\\\" and character.\\\"Regional to Texas. It is brewed under license by Miller Brewing Co.\" Fort Worth Fort WorthRegional to Texas. It is brewed under license by Miller Brewing Co.\" Fort Worth TX.\" TX.\"Regional to Texas. It is brewed under license by Miller Brewing Co.\" Fort Worth TX.\"43755,35.3'),
(559, 'Bud Dry', 8, 96, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Introduced in 1989 Bud Dry is the first dry-brewed beer produced by an American brewer. It is brewed with select hops, grains and barley malt, which results in a lighter body and less-sweet taste. As with all Anheuser-Busch beers, it is cold-filtered for a smooth draft taste, but then goes through a second cold-filtered finishing process to provide its unique taste.'),
