(585, 'Highland Scottish Ale', 1, 15, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'While hugely popular in Scotland, this style of beer escapes most North Americans. Designed and brewed by the Scottish punk rocker David â€œMaltyâ€ Macanulty, this creamy, nutty, malty, dark ale is true to its origins. David drives James crazy over this beer, insisting on rigid fermentation temperatures, traditional mild hops for bittering, and even some weird caramelizing ritual as the kettle is being filled. The beer continues to undergo subtle evolutionary changes because the stubborn Scottish bastard will never be satisfied.'),
(586, 'Precipitation Pilsner', 7, 77, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'A true North German Style Pilsner. Light in body and packed full of Czech Saaz hops. The distinctive Pilsner aroma and dry, refreshing taste make a great accompaniment to a hot Vanouver day.'),
(587, 'Fruit Lambics', 11, 121, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'These authentic Belgian-style ales are intensely sour, dry and complex. All three of the lambics - Raspberry, Blackberry and Black Cherry - are aged in oak casks for more than one year. 15 kg, give or take, of whole unpasteurized fruit is added to each 200 litre oak barrel of fermented beer. The naturally occurring wild yeasts cause a second, slow fermentation, breaking down the fruit sugars to total dryness.'),
(588, 'Stoudt\'s Double India Pale Ale', 3, 32, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Strong, full-bodied ale with an intense hop character and deep golden color'),
