(661, 'Premium Beer', 7, 77, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Bitburger guarantees premium quality and enjoyment. Drawing on almost 200 years of expertise, the full-bodied, light, Bitburger Premium Beer is of course brewed according to the German Purity Law. Its popular, dry-finished, hoppy taste has secured Bitburger Premium Beer position as Germany\'s no. 1 draught beer.-http://www.bitburger.com/bitburger_beers/bitburger_premium_beer/product_bitburger_premium_beer/index.html\"4567Hell\'s BelleHell\'s Belle'),
(662, 'Foster\'s Special Bitter', 1, 3, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'http://www.fostersbeer.com/home.aspx?fullbrowser=h'),
(663, 'Honey Moon Summer Ale', 11, 116, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'The Gold Medal-winning Honey Moon Summer Ale is a classic summer ale made even better with real clover honey, fresh orange peel and both pale and white wheat malts.  Proff that brewing the perfect summer ale is a true art.'),
(664, 'Staropramen', 7, 77, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Classic famous czech beer from Praha, one of the best beers of the world'),
(665, 'Bad Penny', 3, 38, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'This dark brown ale is slightly sweet with a caramel and dark fruit finish. A show case of fine English malts, floor malted the old way. We use pale, chocolate, and crystal malts to produce a complex, but easy drinking dark ale. Very reminescent of northern English ales.'),
(666, 'Antler Brown Ale', 3, 38, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'This traditional American style brown ale has medium body with a sweet Carastan maltiness. A rich deep chocolate color, our Antler Brown Ale is mildly hopped with Mt. Hood hops. Check out the Antler tap handle... locally grown! This has been our most popular beer over the years... a very easy drinking brew.'),
(667, 'Navigator Golden Ale', 3, 37, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Another one of our most popular brews. Navigator Gold has a crisp and slighly hoppy finish. It\'s cold filtered and moderately carbonated.'),
(668, 'Cliffhanger Light Ale', 8, 96, '3', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Our lightest brew, this ale has a lower alcohol content than other Barley Creek brews. The Munich malt and Saaz and Hallertau hops give it a distinct German profile. Refreshing with a clean, dry finish.'),
(669, 'Angler Black Lager', 7, 86, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Dark and delightful, this is an easy-drinking brew. Once a seasonal favorite now we brew it all the time as part of our variety case. Brewed with five different malts and three different hops, then pitched with Bavarian lager yeast.'),
(670, 'Rescue IPA', 3, 31, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Hopped four separate times with pure Centennial hops for one of the hoppiest brews around. With a nice dry finish, Rescue IPA is our Mug Club\'s favorite.'),
(671, 'Iron Arm Belgian Style Wheat', 5, 67, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'A Belgian-style summer favorite. Malted wheat, Pale, Munich and Cara Vienna malt, then moderately hopped with Saaz and a double dose of Hallertau. Served unfiltered with an orange wedge, this is fun in a glass.'),
(672, 'Mountaineer Maibock', 7, 91, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'A German style lager. Light in color, with medium to full body and mild hop bitterness.'),
(673, 'Old \'99 Barley Wine', 3, 35, '11', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'First brewed in 1998 to be served on our fifth anniversary (December 15, 1999), this beer just gets better every year. And, every year around our anniversary, we brew a new vintage. With an original gravity of 1099, this Barley Wine is dark and sweet, and is served in a snifter like an after-dinner drink. You\'ll want to savor it slowly.'),
(674, 'Saranac Adirondack Lager', 8, 95, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Our classic German lager has a perfect balance of caramel malt sweetness. Look for a rich, amber color and medium body.'),
(675, 'Organic Ale', 3, 37, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'A delicately flavored golden ale in which subtle fruity esters from the Samuel Smith yeast strain interact with a background of maltiness and fresh hops.'),
(676, 'Founders Imperial Stout', 3, 43, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'A fine companion to end a meal or relax in front of the hearth with, this robust ale will cellar well for years. Brewed with ten varieties of malted barley this stout is extremely smooth, complex and rich in body. We recommend serving at cellar temperature. Sit back and enjoy its richness and complexity, your about to drink the ultimate winter warmer.'),
(677, 'Founders Pale Ale', 3, 26, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'A testament to Cascade hops in a bottle. Our medium-bodied, Pale Ale has a distinctive floral hop aroma and refreshing citrus flavor. Founders Pale Ale has a slight malty sweetness with a balanced hop finish. A perfect beer to enjoy while mowing the lawn, boating, grilling with friends or just taking it easy.'),
(678, 'Founders Black Rye', 11, 119, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'This beer will surprise you with a big hop flavor and a toasty sweet aroma. Pours black from the chocolate and de-bitterized black rye malts. This ale is medium bodied and is well flavored with hints of toffee, nutty undertones and a dry crisp finish.'),
(679, 'Founders Breakfast Stout', 3, 43, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'You\'ve got to love coffee to truly appreciate this phenomenal brew. Brewed with an abundance of flaked oats, bitter and sweetened imported chocolates, Sumatra and Kona coffee. Breakfast Stout has an intense fresh roasted coffee nose toped with a cinnamon colored frothy head that seems to never fade and makes you wish breakfast could last forever.'),
(680, 'Rubaeus', 11, 121, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'As promised Founders Brewing Company has created something unlike the rest. Amongst this summers over croweded race to cloudy wheat beers, we have decided to embark down a path all our own. Using only fresh rasberries, rubaeus translates into intese flavors combined with a no hesitation malt bill. In fermentation we add fresh rasberries at five separate stages to achieve the ulttimate balance between tartness and sweetness.'),
(681, 'Curmudgeon', 1, 13, '9', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'This Old Ale conjures up thoughts of classic sea fairing ports, there local pubs and the weathered fisherman that frequent them. In traditional style Curmudgeon is brewed with an intense focus on the malt bill creating a very strong, rich, malty characteristic and a sweetness indicative of its cousin the barleywine. We are especially proud of the balance in this beer making it deceptively smooth and drinkable at 9.3% alcohol by volume.'),
(682, 'Founders Kentucky Breakfast', 3, 43, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'A bit of backwoods pleasure without the banjo. This stout is brewed with a hint of coffee and vanilla then aged in oak bourbon barrels. Our process ensures that strong bourbon undertones come through in the finish in every batch we brew. We recommend decanting at room temperature and best enjoyed in a brandy snifter.'),
(683, 'Founders Devil Dancer', 3, 32, '13', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Founders most complex, most innovative, most feared and yet most revered ale produced. Massive in complexity the huge malt character balances the insane amount of alpha\'s used to create this monster. More IBU\'s than any brewery has documented, more than you would believe and dry-hopped for twenty-six days straight with a combination of 10 hop varieties. Dangerously drinkable and deliciously evil. We dare you to dance with the Devil.'),
(684, 'Founders Red\'s Rye', 11, 119, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Pours a spectacular crimson red with a creamy tan head. Brewed with four varieties of Belgian caramel malts imparting a sweet richness. Red\'s Rye is impressively balanced with its hop bitterness and huge citrus bouquet achieved from the immense amarillo dry hop. The generous amount of malted rye used accentuates a spicy crisp finish.'),
(685, 'Saranac Pale Ale', 3, 26, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'A beer that would make the English jealous! This true English Pale Ale is rich and fruity, yet finishes crisp. You\'ll love the copper amber color and medium body.'),
(686, 'Saranac Brown Ale', 3, 38, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'This Brown Ale is brewed with American malt and hops, and traditional ale yeast. Look for a sweet, chocolaty taste, with balanced bitterness resulting in a full flavored but smoothly drinkable beer.'),
(687, 'Saranac India Pale Ale', 3, 31, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A hop lover\'s delight. In the India Pale Ale tradition this brew is very hoppy in both aroma and flavor from the generous amounts of cascade hops used in brewing. Look for a medium to full body and golden straw color.'),
(688, 'Saranac Black Forest', 7, 86, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A Bavarian black beer with distinctive carmel malt sweetness and rich creamy trademark head. Flavorful, yet smooth'),
(689, 'Saranac Lager', 8, 95, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'A simple well-made Classic American Lager brewed with only choice ingredients. It is extremely mellow refreshingly smooth, glass after glass.'),
(690, 'Pomegranate Wheat', 11, 121, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'This wholesome combination of unfiltered wheat beer and real pomegranate juice makes a smooth refreshing beer with all the goodness of pomegranate. Look for a light body with a slight tart finish and golden straw color.'),
(691, 'Saranac Belgian White', 5, 67, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Our Belgian Style White beer is smooth, tangy and very thirst quenching. Brewed with a delicate combination of oats, wheat and barley malt, we season it ever so lightly with hops. Then we add sprinklings of coriander and orange peel for a refreshing brew with a citrus aroma. Don\'t be fooled by the cloudy appearance, that\'s expected of a classic Belgian-style \\Whitbier\\\" or white beer.\"'),
(692, 'Saranac Summer Ale', 11, 116, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'ith more than 2,800 bodies of water in the Adirondacks, it\'s not too hard to find a sunny place to relax, rest your feet and look out over the water. To celebrate summer in the Adirondacks, we\'ve brewed a beer with generous amounts of wheat malt for a light, refreshing taste. Look for subtle hints of lemon.'),
(693, 'Saranac Golden Pilsner', 7, 77, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Saranac Pilsener is a light bodied American Wheat Beer that is judiciously hopped with Cascade and Tettnang hops. \\Dry-Hopping\\\" imparts the distinctive hop aroma and finish. Look for a smooth'),
(694, 'Saranac Octoberfest', 7, 84, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Saranac Octoberfest is a med-bodied, copper colored lager. It\'s rich, malty taste is subtly balanced by Saaz and Tettnang hops. The beer is aged slowly in the tradition of the Octoberfest beers of Munich.'),
(695, 'Saranac Pumpkin Ale', 11, 123, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Saranac Pumpkin Ale is brewed with Pumpkin, Cinnamon, Allspice, Cloves, Ginger and Vanilla. Look for a full-body and amber color. We\'re sure you\'ll enjoy this special brew!'),
(696, 'Saranac Season\'s Best', 8, 95, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Brewed with a special blend of domestic and Belgian malts for a delicate nut-like character, you\'ll love this Lager\'s rich taste and signature hop aroma. The exceptional full-bodied taste reflects our Brewery\'s extraordinary commitment to brewing beers of the highest standard of quality.'),
(697, 'Saranac Caramel Porter', 2, 25, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Saranac Caramel Porter is a Robust, flavorful porter Reminiscent of a by-gone era. True to brewing tradition, we\'ve used dark caramel malt, as well as Fuggles and East Kent Goldings hops for smooth, yet slightly bitter, roasted flavor, look for hints of the real caramel used in brewing this delicious beer!'),
(698, 'Saranac Black Diamond Bock', 7, 90, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Saranac Black Diamond Bock is a rich, malty brew, made with traditional German malts and hops and fermented with a lager yeast. Aged for months for a rich but smooth malty taste. A nice reward for enduring your winter months.'),
(699, 'Saranac Oatmeal Stout', 1, 21, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Saranac Oatmeal Stout is brewed with a delicate balance of the finest grown oats, selected hops, and our traditional ale yeast. Look for a sweet, dark chocolate and roasted taste.'),
(700, 'Roggen Bock', 7, 90, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Brewed in the tradition of great German Bock beers with only German malts and hops, using 20% rye, malt to give it a distinctive spicy, yet smooth character. You\'ll love the rich flavors and deep red color of this unique German Brew.'),
(701, 'Saranac Nut Brown Ale', 3, 38, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Saranac Nut Brown Ale\'s soft mellow malt character is rich and smooth with a medium body. Look for hints of toasted malt flavor, slight hop bitterness and amber brown color.'),
(702, 'Saranac Mocha Stout', 3, 42, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Combines the rich roasted flavor of our traditional stout with a deep, robust mocha. Look for a full-bodied taste with a crescendo of complex flavor notes.'),
(703, 'Saranac Single Malt', 1, 15, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'We use 100% Scottish Maris Otter Malt. Traditionally used in the distilling industry. The combination of the Scottish Malt and slow aging process produces a unique brew as distinctive as single malt whiskey with a flavor than any other beer.'),
(704, 'Saranac Belgian Ale', 5, 72, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Saranac Belgian Ale is Deliciously Fruity. It is brewed with a generous amount of Belgian Aromatic Malt, Hand selected hops, and a traditional Belgian ale yeast. Brewed in the \\Trappist Style\\\".\"'),
(705, 'Saranac Mountain Ale', 11, 121, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'This Delicious Fruity ale is brewed with blackberries, raspberries and sweetened with a touch of blueberry honey. Light and refreshing.With a reddish-Amber color, be sure to look for the ale bitter and berry sweetness. Enjoy!'),
(706, 'Saranac Bock', 7, 90, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Bock is not from the bottom of the barrel! It is a rich malty beer brewed with traditional German ingredients and aged for months to give it a smooth malty character. Look for a rich full-bodied beer.'),
(707, 'Saranac Extra Special Bitter', 1, 5, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Bitters are popular pub beers in England and are closely related to the more well known pales ales. Saranac Extra Special Bitter has a rich, malty taste balanced by the pleasant bitterness of Williamette Hops. The finish is dry with a hint of the Foral English Fuggle and Spicy Saaz hop. Enjoy!'),
(708, 'Saranac Imperial IPA', 3, 32, '9', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Saranac Imperial IPA is part our new High Peak Series, a line of beers that are bigger, more complex and flavorful'),
(709, 'Saranac Imperial Stout', 3, 43, '9', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Saranac Imperial Stout is part of our \\High Peaks Series'),
(710, 'Saranac Scotch Ale', 1, 15, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'This Scotch Ale is a full-bodied, malty sweet ale. True to Scottish brewing tradition, this malty flavor and deep copper brown color are a result of Scottish two row malt and roasted barley.'),
(711, 'Stony Face Red Ale', 3, 33, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Hoppyâ€™s gift to those who like their beers Malty. Dark Caramel and Chocolate Malts lend their deep crimson silkiness, and judicious additions of Nugget and Cascade hops give just enough bitterness for balance. Ask your serverâ€™s favorite beer and itâ€™s probably this one.'),
(712, 'Humbles Blond Ale', 3, 37, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Our lightest beer in body and color, Humbles has proven to be our most popular offering.'),
(713, 'Heat Seeker Hefe', 4, 50, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'A Bavarian style Hefeweizen, a cloudy brew with slight hints of bannana and clove.  Light and refreshing.'),
(714, 'Catalina Common Lager', 8, 95, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'This copper colored lager is brewed with hybrid yeast that ferments at warmer temps, giving that clean refreshing taste of a lager with the slight fruitiness of an ale.'),
(715, 'Spitfire Best Bitter', 1, 3, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'An English style ale, copper in color with subtle English malt hints balanced nicely with fresh Washington grown Yakima Valley hops.'),
(716, 'Afterburner IPA', 3, 31, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'A hop lover\'s delight!  Our I.P.A. is loaded with Ahtanum, Tohmahawk, Palisade, East Kent, Goldings and finished with the ever popular Cascades, balanced with generous amounts of floor malted crisp Maris Otter barley.'),
(717, 'Hop Henge Imperial IPA', 3, 32, '9', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'HOP HENGE IMPERIAL IPA â€“ The Ultimate in Hop Innovation Hop Henge Imperial IPA returns to the Bond Street Series line-up this April in extreme fashion. Staying true to the experimental nature of the series and the â€œnever settleâ€ philosophy of Deschutes our brewers went back to the drawing board to create an amplified version of last yearâ€™s monument to hops. our brewers went back to the drawing board to create an amplified version of last yearâ€™s monument to hops.Head Brewer Brett Porter says â€œThis is a truly exciting and groundbreaking beer. We reformulated everything about the hop recipe to give Hop Henge an extraordinary aroma and flavor similar to a fresh hop beer.â€ In addition to the Cascade and Centennial hops â€œThis is a truly exciting and groundbreaking beer. We reformulated everything about the hop recipe to give Hop Henge an extraordinary aroma and flavor similar to a fresh hop beer.â€ In addition to the Cascade and Centennial hopsHead Brewer Brett Porter says â€œThis is a truly exciting and groundbreaking beer. We reformulated everything about the hop recipe to give Hop Henge an extraordinary aroma and flavor similar to a fresh hop beer.â€ In addition to the Cascade and Centennial hops Deschutes Brewery is experimenting with a hop variety so new that it has yet to be named. Deschutes Brewery is experimenting with a hop variety so new that it has yet to be named.When one of our brewers suggested we name our new IPA Hop Henge only with hop bales.  We were up for the challenge and even though the weather did not want to cooperate only with hop bales.  We were up for the challenge and even though the weather did not want to cooperateWhen one of our brewers suggested we name our new IPA Hop Henge only with hop bales.  We were up for the challenge and even though the weather did not want to cooperate we pulled it off and threw a party afterwards. we pulled it off and threw a party afterwards.'),
(718, 'Barnstormer Brown Ale', 3, 38, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'As the name implies, a rich deep brown ale in color with dark amber highlights.  The flavor is slightly sweet with hints of nuts and toffee finishing smooth with no after taste.'),
(719, 'Peacemaker Porter', 2, 25, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'A robust porter in style, a dark and full bodied ale with hints of roasted barley and flavors of coffee and bitter sweet chocolate on the palate.'),
(720, 'Sick Duck Imperial Stout', 3, 43, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'A rich and very dark Imperial Stout that has a complex flavor profile with hints of molasses and caramel.  Brewed in July to allow time for aging, Sick Duck finishes very smooth for such a big beer.'),
(721, 'Bube\'s Stout', 3, 42, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'This dark full bodied stout is perfect with a meal or as a meal. Rolled oats give this beer an enjoyable mouthfeel while chocolate and roasted malts lend to its distinctive flavor.'),
(722, 'Bube\'s Kiwi-Strawberry Wheat', 11, 121, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'The perfect thirst quenching summertime ale. The subtle flavor of kiwi and strawberry blend with traditional German wheat and hops. Great for a hot summer day.'),
(723, 'Bube\'s Brown Ale', 3, 38, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Another one of our first recipes, which we have improved with experience. This ale is pleasantly malty with nutty and toffee like undertones. East Kent Golding hops were used to compliment this English style ale.'),
(724, 'Bube\'s Hefeweizen', 4, 50, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'This traditional German-style wheat beer is rich in banana and clove undertones, with a wonderful frothy head.'),
(725, 'Bube\'s India Pale Ale (IPA)', 3, 31, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Bube\'s rendition of this classic style is made with fine 2-row malted barley and West Coast hops. A wonderful malt finish with a delicate citrus aroma, reminiscent of its Old-World cousin.'),
(726, 'Scratch #7 2008', 4, 55, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Red and white wheat combined with darker malts add body to this hazy, unfiltered ale.  Fermented with the same yeast as DreamWeaver Wheat replicating the pepper, clove and all-spice flavors found in our year-round beer.'),
(727, 'Scratch #11 2008', 1, 3, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Next up, we present Scratch Beer #11-2008, a Bitter. Back in the day, we used to brew a little number called TrÃ¶egs ESB. Even though this beer was retired almost six years ago, we still get numerous TrÃ¶egs old-schoolers (Martha) begging for its return.The Thames Valley ale yeast and the roasted barley create a biscuit flavor with nutty undertones. Combining these flavors with the earthiness of East Kent Golding hops creates one hell of a fine session beer. Take in the deep mahogany beauty of this beer and breathe in the full hoppy nose. Itâ€™s not the ESB464710,210.2This grand cru has been lovingly aged since late-February yet still unleashes the slightest hint of alcohol heat. yet still unleashes the slightest hint of alcohol heat.'),
(728, 'Scratch #8 2008', 5, 61, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Revisiting Scratch #3, we take the same Tripel recipe, add beet and cane sugars to the kettle, and run the wort through our hopback brimming with juniper berries, coriander and yarrow flowers.Inspired by the herbaceous nose of gin the berries and flowers give a slight pine/citrus aroma with floral undertones. Scratch #8 has a dry the berries and flowers give a slight pine/citrus aroma with floral undertones. Scratch #8 has a dryInspired by the herbaceous nose of gin the berries and flowers give a slight pine/citrus aroma with floral undertones. Scratch #8 has a dry yeasty finish and noticeable alcohol warming when consumed.\" yeasty finish and noticeable alcohol warming when consumed.\"Inspired by the herbaceous nose of gin the berries and flowers give a slight pine/citrus aroma with floral undertones. Scratch #8 has a dry yeasty finish and noticeable alcohol warming when consumed.\"46495,15.14651Sundown WheatSundown Wheat'),
(729, 'Oaked Arrogant Bastard Ale', 3, 30, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Arrogant Bastard Ale aged in oak barrels.'),
(730, 'Hansa Imported Dortmunder', 8, 95, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Surviving beer from the Dortmunder Hansa-Brauerei before being acquired by Actien.'),
(731, 'Hoppy Hefe', 4, 50, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'It is a nice example of a Hefeweizen.'),
(732, 'Bourbon Barrel Smoked Porter', 2, 25, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Think of Guinness but with a \\smooth bite\\\" to it. This is a wonder beer for those of us who enjoy a porter.\"'),
(733, 'Cask Hefe', 4, 50, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'It is a good clean hefe.'),
(734, 'Raison D\'Etre', 3, 29, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A deep, mahogany ale brewed with beet sugar, green raisins, and Belgian-style yeast. As complex as a fine, red wine. Voted \\American Beer of the Year\\\" in January 2000 by Malt Advocate Magazine.\"');
