(824, 'Existential', 3, 35, '11', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Consider it an extremely hoppy barleywine, or a really big IPA. Either way, ten hop additions contribute to its lush and intriguing body. Aggressive dry-hopping brings a strong citrus character to the aroma. The flavor and smell of orange-blossoms pervade throughout the experience.'),
(825, 'Pilgrim\'s Dole', 3, 35, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Pilgrimâ€™s Dole is a barleywine-style ale made with fifty percent wheat malt, or what we at New Holland call a wheatwine. Pilgrimâ€™s Dole blends warming and slightly sweet flavors with a unique caramelized character. It would be an excellent accent to nutty dishes, fruit crisps or creme brulee.'),
(826, 'Cabin Fever', 3, 38, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Robust in character yet smooth in delivery, Cabin Fever is a roasty brown ale and a hearty, comforting companion for long, mind-bending winters. Its rye, roast and raisin notes play off a subtle caramel sweetness and culminate in a dry finish. Excellent with roasts, stews, caramelized onions and snowfall.'),
(827, 'Ichabod', 3, 35, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Ichabod combines malted barley and real pumpkin with cinnamon and nutmeg in a delicious and inviting brew. A rewarding complement to many dishes, Ichabod pairs well with autumnal foods such as poultry and root vegetables. After dinner, try it with your favorite dessert!'),
(828, 'Zoomer', 11, 116, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A refreshing wheat ale, Zoomer is brewed to quench your summer thirst. American-grown wheat provides Zoomer\'s straw color and its soft, clean body. With subtle, yet flavorful hints of citrus fruit in its finish, Zoomer is the perfect companion to all things summer. Food pairings include artisan cheeses, fresh greens, fish and chicken.'),
(829, 'Night Tripper', 3, 43, '11', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Night Tripper is an Imperial Stout for a Fat Tuesday release. Dark, mysterious and poetic, Night Tripper\'s abundance of roasted malts, combined with flaked barley create a rich, roasty beer with deeply intense and lush flavors. Night Tripper\'s layered, nuanced tones invite intrigue and reward a curious palate.'),
(830, 'Woody\'s Light', 3, 26, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Our take on the classic light golden ale, with crisp refreshing flavors.'),
(831, 'Grateful Red', 3, 33, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Making Jerry proud with an amber ale that\'s slightly malty and very tasty.'),
(832, 'Lost Sailor', 3, 31, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'A Hop Head\'s dream beer, enough said.'),
(833, 'Sully\'s Irish Stout', 3, 42, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Put on your kilt and enjoy this roasted, dark, malty and slightly sweet beer.'),
(834, 'Pirate\'s Porter', 3, 29, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Arrr this be a dark beer with strong notes of coffee and chocolate flavors.'),
(835, 'Marzen', 8, 95, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'The name says it all, you want German this is it.'),
(836, '.38 Special Bitter', 1, 3, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Don\'t let the name scare you, this is an easy drinker, slightly sweet and bitter.'),
(837, 'Pete\'s Wicked Strawberry Blonde', 11, 121, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Pete\'s Wicked Strawberry Blonde is truly a unique beer experience. Reward yourself with our golden lager made of the finest pale and wheat malts and Cluster Hops, with a kiss of natural strawberry flavor.'),
(838, 'Pete\'s Rally Cap Ale', 11, 116, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'The key ingredient to a good summer is a GREAT brew! Born to play, Pete\'s Wicked Rally Cap Ale is crafted with a special blend of pale and wheat malts, Mt. Hood hops and a smack of natural lemon. Get in the game... Get Wicked!'),
(839, 'Pete\'s Wicked Wanderlust Cream Ale', 11, 113, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Peteâ€™s winter seasonal Wanderlust Cream Ale, is a velvety smooth brew offering endless fascination. Peteâ€™s Wicked Wanderlust Cream Ale is a light amber brew with a rhapsody of Cluster hops and select Munich and wheat malts. The rich, creamy taste invites you on a journey of wonderment and intrigue. Sit back. Enjoy the ride.'),
(840, 'Wailua', 11, 116, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Wailua is Hawaiian for two fresh water streams mingling. This was just the inspiration we needed for our Limited Release wheat ale brewed with tropical passion Fruit. A refreshing citrusy, sun-colored ale with the cool taste of Hawaii.'),
(841, 'Buck Naked', 8, 96, '3', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'An American-style \\light beer\\\".  Formulated to appeal to those who prefer a lighter tasting brew.\"'),
(842, 'Big Buck Beer', 3, 26, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A standard American-style beer and our flagship brand.  A small amount of corn is added to the grist to give the brew a smooth character.  Features a rich, golden color and a light malt character balanced with a mild dose of hops.'),
(843, 'Raspberry Wheat', 11, 116, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'An American wheat beer made with malted barley and malted wheat.  Lightly flavored with pure fruit to impart a subtle raspberry nose, a delicate fruit flavor and a slight pink hue.'),
(844, 'Nut Brown', 3, 38, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'The rich mahogany hue of the Nut Brown is the first thing you will notice. You\'ll find subtle hints of both chocolate and coffee. We delicately blend chocolate and caramel malts with four others to make this flavorful, easy drinking beer. The malt character will appeal to those looking for a moderately dark ale, but the smoothness is what will surprise all.'),
(845, 'Cascazilla', 3, 33, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'The name CascaZilla is a play on both the name of our local Cascadilla Gorge and the monster amounts of Cascade hops in this beer. This red ale gets its distinctive color from a healthy portion of caramel malt, which also lends some body and sweetness to the beer. The predominant flavor and aroma of this beer, however, is brought to you by the fresh American hops. If you haven\'t done so yet, treat yourself to Ithaca Beer\'s new monstrously hoppy Red Ale.'),
(846, 'Flower Power India Pale Ale', 3, 31, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Enjoy the clover honey hue and tropical nose. Simultaneously Punchy and soothing with a big body and a finish that boasts pineapple and grapefruit. Flower power is hopped and dry-hopped five different times throughout the brewing and fermentation process.'),
(847, 'Partly Sunny', 11, 116, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Partly Sunny is hazy-straw colored wheat beer with coriander, and generous amounts of lemon zest. It\'s a light refreshing beer with a subtle spicy start and a smooth citrus finish.'),
(848, 'Rye Squared', 3, 32, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Double the malt, double the hops, and double the flavor of the original Rye Pale Ale recipe. (Hence the name Rye Squared.) With its mammoth hop aroma, bitterness and flavor, this beer is not for the faint at heart. The Rye Squared clocks in at a hefty 9.5% ABV so double your pleasure and double your fun because Terrapin went a little crazy with this one!'),
(849, 'Southern Tier Porter', 2, 25, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Porter is our darkest beer, but not necessarily our strongest.  It is widely held that the darker the beer, the stronger the beer, but this is a summarily false.  The contribution of color comes directly from the color of malt that we use.  Some malt is oasted to achieve dark color and coffee-like flavor which in turn get transferred to the beer.Our Porter is ruchly complex with overtones of chocolate and expresso beans followed by a subtle flavor of hops.  It\'s a nourishing beer without being too sweet or filling.\"4875Southern Tier TripelSouthern Tier Tripel4876Old Man Winter AleOld Man Winter Ale'),
(850, 'Hop Sun', 11, 116, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Pour Hop Sun Summer Wheat Beer into a pint glass, give it a long whiff and youâ€™ll realize that this isnâ€™t your average wheatbeer. Filtered to a golden clarity and dry-hopped to perfection, Hop Sun is a fantastic session ale in which flavors of wheat, barley and hops commingle to a refreshing and zesty conclusion. Hints of lemon and sweet malts waft to the fore as a touch of bitterness contributes to Hop Sunâ€™s bright finish. Enjoy Hop Sun all summer long as a perfect balance to your outdoor recreation. Summer never tasted so good.'),
(851, 'Unearthly Imperial India Pale Ale', 3, 32, '11', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'At the Southern Tier Brewing Company, vigorously hopped beer is our standard and inspiration. We continue a commitment to innovation with our most aggressive offering yet. Unearthly is a manifestation of the brewerâ€™s craft'),
(852, 'Pumking Imperial Pumpkin Ale', 11, 123, '9', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Pumking is an ode to PÃºca, a creature of Celtic folklore, who is both feared and respected by those who believe in it. PÃºca is said to waylay travelers throughout the night, tossing them on its back, and providing them the ride of their lives, from which they return forever changed. Brewed in the spirit of All Hallows Eve, a time of the year when spirits can make contact with the physical world and when magic is most potent. Pour Pumking into a goblet and allow itâ€™s alluring spirit to overflow. As spicy aromas present themselves, let itâ€™s deep copper color entrance you as your journey into this mystical brew has just begun. As the first drops touch your tongue a magical spell will bewitch your taste buds making it difficult to escape the Pumking.'),
(853, 'Choklat', 3, 43, '11', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'The Popol Vuh, the sacred book of the Maya, unfolds a complex web of mystery around a beverage known as xocoatl (ch-co-atle). At Southern Tier, weâ€™re not surprised that hieroglyphs of the ancient Maya depict chocolate being poured for rulers and gods. Even through the many voyages of Columbus, the mystical bean remained nothing more than a strange currency of the native peoples.Moving through centuries the circular journey of cacao has been realized in our brewing house the circular journey of cacao has been realized in our brewing houseMoving through centuries the circular journey of cacao has been realized in our brewing house encompassing the complexity of the darkest encompassing the complexity of the darkestMoving through centuries the circular journey of cacao has been realized in our brewing house encompassing the complexity of the darkest bitter-sweet candy together with the original frothy cold beverage of the ancient Maya to bring to you our Blackwater Series Choklat Stout. We have combined the finest ingredients to tempt your senses & renew the power & interrelation of history in every bottle. bitter-sweet candy together with the original frothy cold beverage of the ancient Maya to bring to you our Blackwater Series Choklat Stout. We have combined the finest ingredients to tempt your senses & renew the power & interrelation of history in every bottle.4890Weizen Bam BiÃ¨reWeizen Bam BiÃ¨re4890Weizen Bam BiÃ¨re4.54.5'),
(854, 'E.S. Bam', 5, 74, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'An Extra Special Farmhouse Ale. A Bam celebration of excess. More malt, more hops, same vivacious personality.'),
(855, 'Bam Noire', 5, 74, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Dark, smooth, delicious.  Aromas of worn leather and cool autumn nights. Notes of sweet plum and toasted raisin, hints of coffee and cacao. Lingering tart and refreshing finish.  Only available for a few short months.  Not to be missed.'),
(856, 'Madrugada Obscura', 3, 42, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'A Belgian inspired stout that is as dark as a moonless midnight, brimming of roasted malts and bitter hops. It will keep you good company in all places, be thay light or dark.'),
(857, 'Fuego del Otono', 3, 33, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'To catch a bit of soft radiance in each bottle, we wait for fall colors to begin their bright and fleeting glow before brewing this wonderful ale under their autumn fire. Gentle amber malt blend smooth caramel notes, gently lapping against a shore of distant forgotten spice. A beer to sip, contemplate and enjoy.'),
(858, 'Terrapin Monk\'s Revenge', 5, 72, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'This Belgian IPA has a malt bill of a Belgian Tripel and a hop bill of a Double IPA. The yeast I chose for this beer comes from one of the 7 Trappist breweries.Believe it or not this is the first time in my professional brewing career that I have used dextrose (corn syrup) in a Terrapin brew. True to style no doubt. this is the first time in my professional brewing career that I have used dextrose (corn syrup) in a Terrapin brew. True to style no doubt.4898Rickard\'s White AleRickard\'s White Ale'),
(859, 'Dirty Blond', 11, 116, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Made with unmalted wheat, coriander and orange peel to help you live smart and enjoy everyday!'),
(860, 'Vanilla Java Porter', 2, 25, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A robust porter made with chocolate malt.  We blend it with Vanilla and Java beans, and balance it with U.S. Golding Hops.');
INSERT INTO `beer` (`id_BEE`, `name_BEE`, `cat_BEE`, `style_BEE`, `deg_BEE`, `filepath_BEE`, `desc_BEE`) VALUES
(861, 'Voodoo Vator', 7, 92, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'This one is black and sweet!  Its malty character is derived from two carmel malts along with Munich malt to create the smoothest high gravity beer this side of the \\pond\\\".\"'),
(862, 'Salvation', 3, 31, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Our version of India Pale Ale. Brewed with European malts and Northwest hops and then generously Dry Hopped with Cascade Hops for a nice citrus finish. Truly a Salvation for all Hop Heads.'),
(863, 'Rost', 3, 33, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Rost (pronounced Roast) is a German word for Amber. Our Amber gets its coppery color from Pilsner. Munich and Caramel malts. Its rich malty sweetness is perfectly balanced by a slight hop finish and creamy head.'),
(864, 'MAI-BOCK', 7, 90, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A traditional german helles bock, golden in color and brewed with only the finest imported malt and hops. The distinct malty sweetness is balanced by a pronounced hop finish. Brewed to Welcome the Spring Season.'),
(865, 'Erik the Red', 3, 33, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'An Irish style red (amber) beer. Light in finish but bold in taste. Melanoidin malt is added for the red color and the spicy finish comes through from the Chinook hops.'),
(866, 'Nagelweiss', 11, 116, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'This German style wheat beer contains about 50% malted wheat and is balanced with Hallertau hops. This beer finishes low in gravity so the final taste is light on the palette and extremely drinkable. This is sure to be a favorite with first time and long time wheat beer drinkers.'),
(867, 'Final Absolution', 5, 72, '9', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Dragonmead\'s signature product! This is the ultimate Belgian style. The very high gravity of this beer is balanced by the smoothness of its finish. Banana and Clove aromas come from the Belgian yeast strain combining with the generous dose of Belgian Candi Sugar. The Saaz hops help to give this beer a balanced bitterness with no noticeable hop aroma.'),
(868, 'Armageddon Grand Cru', 5, 72, '12', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Grand Crus are traditionally known as \\The best beer that a brewery makes.\\\" This Belgian-style quad lives up to that name and then some. Available once a year'),
(869, 'Bronze Griffin', 5, 72, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Sweet Orange Blossom Honey is combined with Belgian two-row malted barley and Munich malt to create another Belgian classic. Tetternger and E. Kent Goldings hops are added to round out the finish of this beer. The aroma of the honey remains without the sugary sweetness.'),
(870, 'Dead Monk Abbey Ale', 5, 72, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'This Belgian beer is brewed in the style of the Trappist Monks. Belgian Candi Sugar, Pilsen, Aromatic and Caramunich malts are balance by E. Kent Goldings, Mt. Hood and Saaz hops to construct a \\Big Beer\\\". Traditional White Beer Yeast is used to make this beer have a large mouth-feel and lingering spice notes in the finish.\"'),
(871, 'Broken Paddle', 3, 31, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'If you like your beer on the bitter side then this one\'s for you. This American Style IPA uses Pale Ale, Munich, and Caramunich malt blest with Cascade, Chinook, Willamette and Centennial (dry hopped) hops to create a brew that is fit for the crazy American hop addicts.'),
(872, 'Crooked Door', 3, 33, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'The American hop Cascade is used to give this brew its classic American Aroma. Pale and Crystal malt from the U.S. are used to give this beer a medium body and high hop flavor. This beer goes down easily and opens the door to a world of microbrewed beers.'),
(873, 'Breath of the Dragon English Bitter', 1, 1, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'This fine English style Best Bitter is made with Imported English Pale Ale, Aromatic and Caramel malts. Galena and Willamette Hops add a moderate bittering level to make this a refreshing example of an English Bitter.'),
(874, 'Righteous Ale', 11, 119, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Righteous Ale is actually a Rye Beer, brewed with a high amount of hops.'),
(875, 'Liberty Nut Brown Ale', 3, 38, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Styled after an English classic, this beer is brewed with American flair. Hearty brown in color and full-bodied, this beer has a distinct chocolate-malt finish.'),
(876, 'Miss Liberty Lager', 8, 95, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'This beer is an all-malt lager, brewed with a subtle blend of German hops. Cool fermentation, followed by extended aging, produces a delicate and mild flavor.'),
(877, 'Liberty Unfiltered Wheat Ale', 11, 116, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'This light ale is an American interpretation of a German classic. It\'s not filtered and has a pleasantly tart flavor. Served with a lemon wedge.'),
(878, 'Liberty Pale Ale', 3, 26, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'This copper-colored ale has an intense bitterness and a floral hop aroma. Hops added during aging contribute to its distinct dryness.'),
(879, 'Liberty Raspberry Wheat Ale', 11, 121, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'This brew combines the mild, tartness of a wheat beer with the flavor of real raspberries. The raspberry flavor is not overpowering. It has a wonderful berry aroma, and is a favorite even among those who claim to \\not like beer\\\".\"'),
(880, 'Beach Bum Blonde Ale', 3, 37, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Beach Bum Blonde Ale is a traditional American blonde ale with a slightly spicy hop note and balanced malty flavor.\"4928Longboard LagerLongboard Lager4928Longboard Lager5.55.5'),
(881, 'Coopers Premium Lager', 8, 95, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Coopers Premium Lager is quite different to the famous Coopers ales.  This lager produces a refreshing flavour with a good balance of malt and hop characters and is brewed using no sugar. With its subtle fruity esters and light golden colour, combined with a judicious blend of Pride of Ringwood and Saaz hops.  This produces a Lager with a crisp malty full flavour.'),
(882, 'Coopers Sparkling Ale', 1, 1, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'The ale by which all others should be measured. With its famous cloudy sediment and its distinctive balance of malt, hops and fruity characters, the old \'Red Label\' is a tasty slice of Coopers history. '),
(883, 'Coopers Original Pale Ale', 1, 1, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Guaranteed to turn heads, this is the beer that inspired a new generation of ale drinkers. With its fruity character, and robust flavour, Coopers Pale Ale is perfect for every occasion. Naturally fermented in the \'Burton-on-Trent\' style a secondary fermentation creates the trademark sediment that gives \'Pale\' its fine cloudy appearance. This cloudy residue can be stirred through the beer by tipping or rolling the bottle before drinking.  a secondary fermentation creates the trademark sediment that gives \'Pale\' its fine cloudy appearance. This cloudy residue can be stirred through the beer by tipping or rolling the bottle before drinking. Pale Ale has no additives or preservatives.\"4932Coopers Mild AleCoopers Mild Ale4932Coopers Mild Ale3.53.5'),
(884, 'Coopers Best Extra Stout', 3, 42, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Now here\'s a beer with punch! Brewed naturally using a top fermentation method dark texture comes from specially roasted black malt.  dark texture comes from specially roasted black malt. Coopers Best Extra Stout contains no additives and no preservatives.\"4934Coopers Premium LightCoopers Premium Light4934Coopers Premium Light2.92.9'),
(885, 'Birell', 8, 96, '1', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Birell has all the hallmarks of a great premium beer, rich colour, full malty flavour and the ability to quench a thirst, with one important difference - virtually no alcohol. Brewed under license in Australia by Coopers Birell is made using only the finest Australian malted barley Birell is made using only the finest Australian malted barleyBrewed under license in Australia by Coopers Birell is made using only the finest Australian malted barley hops and yeast hops and yeastBrewed under license in Australia by Coopers Birell is made using only the finest Australian malted barley hops and yeast with no artificial additives or preservatives. with no artificial additives or preservatives.Coopers Birell may be found in most supermarkets (375ml bottles or cans).\"4936Scratch #13 2008Scratch #13 20084936Scratch #13 20084.94.9'),
(886, 'Scratch #14 2008', 5, 74, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Scratch #14-2008 is our interpretation of a farmhouse aleâ€”a once near-extinct winter-brewed (and summerâ€“imbibed) Belgian ale.Drink it â€˜til the wedding bells chime!\"4938Christoffel BlondChristoffel Blond'),
(887, 'Golden Pheasant', 8, 95, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Brightly filtered, highly carbonated, golden premium-style lager. It is lightly hopped with Polish Lublin hops. The beer will appeal to those who prefer the lighter American style beers.'),
(888, 'Budweiser American Ale', 3, 33, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Budweiser American Ale is brewed with barley from America\'s heartland and dry hopped with Cascade hops from the Pacific Northwest.Available Fall 2008.\"4942Pyramid Hefe WeizenPyramid Hefe Weizen4942Pyramid Hefe Weizen5.25.2Handcrafted with 60% malted wheat (10% more than Bavarian tradition calls for) our award-winning Hefe Weizen is unsurpassed in quality and exceptionally smooth and refreshing for the whole beer experience.\" our award-winning Hefe Weizen is unsurpassed in quality and exceptionally smooth and refreshing for the whole beer experience.\"Handcrafted with 60% malted wheat (10% more than Bavarian tradition calls for) our award-winning Hefe Weizen is unsurpassed in quality and exceptionally smooth and refreshing for the whole beer experience.\"49434,94.9'),
(889, 'Pyramid Apricot Weizen', 11, 121, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Brewed by the original Wheat Beer Pioneers, Pyramid Apricot Weizen Ale is left unfiltered for extra flavor and aroma. The gold medalist of fruit beers Pyramid Apricot Weizen is an adventurous wheat ale that offers the pleasing aroma and flavor of fresh apricots Pyramid Apricot Weizen is an adventurous wheat ale that offers the pleasing aroma and flavor of fresh apricotsThe gold medalist of fruit beers Pyramid Apricot Weizen is an adventurous wheat ale that offers the pleasing aroma and flavor of fresh apricots and smooth and refreshing character for which our wheat beers are known.\" and smooth and refreshing character for which our wheat beers are known.\"The gold medalist of fruit beers Pyramid Apricot Weizen is an adventurous wheat ale that offers the pleasing aroma and flavor of fresh apricots and smooth and refreshing character for which our wheat beers are known.\"49455,55.5Rich amber in color Pyramid Amber Weizen features three different kinds of caramel barley malts and nugget hops resulting in an exceptionally smooth and well-balanced beer that follows in the tradition of our flagship style Pyramid Amber Weizen features three different kinds of caramel barley malts and nugget hops resulting in an exceptionally smooth and well-balanced beer that follows in the tradition of our flagship styleRich amber in color Pyramid Amber Weizen features three different kinds of caramel barley malts and nugget hops resulting in an exceptionally smooth and well-balanced beer that follows in the tradition of our flagship style Pyramid Hefe Weizen.\" Pyramid Hefe Weizen.\"Rich amber in color Pyramid Amber Weizen features three different kinds of caramel barley malts and nugget hops resulting in an exceptionally smooth and well-balanced beer that follows in the tradition of our flagship style Pyramid Hefe Weizen.\"49466,76.7'),
(890, 'Mamma Mia! Pizza Beer', 11, 126, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'An ale flavored with fresh tomatoes, oregano, basil and garlic.'),
(891, 'Thunderstorm', 11, 116, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Our popular summer seasonal brewed with honey, orange, and lemonrass.'),
(892, 'Smoked Helles Lager', 8, 95, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'This light german style Helles Lager was brewed with a small percentage of beechwood smoked malt. Light and delicate east drinking lager'),
(893, 'Redbridge', 8, 95, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Redbridge beer doesnâ€™t need to make promises to stand out from the crowd'),
(894, 'The Viking Belgian-style Dark Strong Ale', 5, 66, '12', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'SPECIAL COMMEMORATIVE BEERTo commemorate the life of a huge-hearted and long-time friend from the homebrewing community Midnight Sun Brewing Company brewed a very special beer in honor of David Yanoshek Midnight Sun Brewing Company brewed a very special beer in honor of David YanoshekTo commemorate the life of a huge-hearted and long-time friend from the homebrewing community Midnight Sun Brewing Company brewed a very special beer in honor of David Yanoshek who was fondly known as â€œYanoâ€.  who was fondly known as â€œYanoâ€. This big strong beer celebrates the abundant life of an incredible man with an enormous yet ever engaging laugh. Yano pursued life with a Viking spirit endless love and boundless energy for family endless love and boundless energy for familyThis big strong beer celebrates the abundant life of an incredible man with an enormous yet ever engaging laugh. Yano pursued life with a Viking spirit endless love and boundless energy for family friends friendsThis big strong beer celebrates the abundant life of an incredible man with an enormous yet ever engaging laugh. Yano pursued life with a Viking spirit endless love and boundless energy for family friends scoutsâ€¦and beer.  scoutsâ€¦and beer. As you lock horns with this commemorative ale toast to Yano. With his incredibly stoic spirit and his irrepressible laugh toast to Yano. With his incredibly stoic spirit and his irrepressible laughAs you lock horns with this commemorative ale toast to Yano. With his incredibly stoic spirit and his irrepressible laugh Yano was the gentle giant who will forever touch our lives. PrÃ¶st!  Yano was the gentle giant who will forever touch our lives. PrÃ¶st! 4958Full Curl Scotch AleFull Curl Scotch Ale'),
(895, 'Mammoth Extra Stout', 3, 42, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Dark and full-bodied, Mammoth Extra Stout boasts a well-rounded melange of rich flavors, including chocolate, caramel, coffee, nut and date. Huge portions of pale and specialty malts give this mammoth brew a complex yet exceptionally smooth palate. Hops provide balance without overpowering the chewy malt profile.'),
(896, 'Bengali Tiger', 3, 31, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Sixpoint Bengali Tiger is reminiscent of the century-old English IPA. In my perspective, many current IPAs suffer from lacking substance'),
(897, 'Ridgeline Amber', 3, 33, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Ridgeline Amber stands out as a stellar, complex choice in a sea of over-simplified amber beers available today. A malty, copper-hued treat from start to finish, Ridgeline begins with a distinctive, estery aroma. Followed with a complex, nutty malt flavor true to its Scottish-style heritage, Ridgeline delivers unparalleled character and dimension. A touch of hops rounds out its silky, full body, highlighting Ridgelineâ€™s subtle but engrossing character. Show your friends that you care about their taste buds by turning them on to our imminently balanced and perfectly complex Ridgeline Amber. Of interest to Great Divide historians â€“ Ridgeline originally debuted at the brewery as Great Divideâ€™s first beer Arapahoe Amber. It was renamed in 2004 to better reflect the Colorado lifestyle that Great Divideâ€™s beers perfectly complement.\" Arapahoe Amber. It was renamed in 2004 to better reflect the Colorado lifestyle that Great Divideâ€™s beers perfectly complement.\"Of interest to Great Divide historians â€“ Ridgeline originally debuted at the brewery as Great Divideâ€™s first beer Arapahoe Amber. It was renamed in 2004 to better reflect the Colorado lifestyle that Great Divideâ€™s beers perfectly complement.\"49625,95.9Prepare yourself for a religious experience\"4963Wild Raspberry AleWild Raspberry Ale4963Wild Raspberry Ale5.65.6'),
(898, 'Le Freak Belgian Style IPA', 5, 72, '9', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Extreme ale converging San Diego-style imperial pale ale and Belgian-style trippel.'),
(899, 'Mount Hill Pale Ale', 1, 1, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'An English pale ale brewed by Otto\'s for the Mount Hill Tavern in Harrisburg Pennsylvania.'),
(900, 'Saison De Brooklyn', 5, 74, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'The second beer of the Brewmaster\'s reserve line, Saison de Brooklyn is brewed in the style produced by old farmhouse breweries in Belgium and France. Well-hopped and fermented to a crisp dryness, Saisons were brewed in the spring to sustain farmers through the summer. Saison de Brooklyn is boldly hoppy, dry and flinty, with a bright spicy, citric aroma and pillowy white head. This beer has remarkable versatility with food, complementing spicy dishes particularly well.'),
(901, 'Yards Brawler', 1, 1, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Boasting superior taste and champion flavor, the Brawler is crafted in the style of English session ales. This malt-forward, ruby colored ale is great for when you want to go a few rounds.'),
(902, 'Yards Philadelphia Pale Ale', 3, 26, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Not to be boastful, but we honestly believe that all other ales pale in comparison to this one. Brewed with pilsner malt, Philadelphia Pale Ale is crisp and hoppy, bursting with citrus flavors and aromas.Philadelphia Pale Ale was named one of the best Pale Ales in the country by the New York Times.\"4972Yards Extra Special AleYards Extra Special Ale'),
(903, 'Yards India Pale Ale', 3, 31, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'IPAs were originally brewed to survive the epic sea voyages from England to India. Ours is no different. Hailing from a firm malt background and loaded through and through with hops, this beer will surely survive the journey from your fridge to your couch.'),
