(906, 'Harpoon Brown Session Ale', 3, 38, '4', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'Harpoon Brown is brewed to accentuate the sweeter, rounder notes derived from six different malts, including a de-husked chocolate malt that adds a hint of chocolate. The blend of these malts produces a beer that is complex and delicious without being heavy. This drinkable beer is perfect as a session beer or paired with foods.This is the first year-round Harpoon beer the brewery has released in almost a decade.  While the craft beer industry has seen a growing trend in \\extreme\\\"\" beers\" the Harpoon Brown Ale has the lowest alcohol content of all Harpoon beers. the Harpoon Brown Ale has the lowest alcohol content of all Harpoon beers.Harpoon Brown Ale will be available in bottles and on draft beginning in March 2007.  An evening of celebrations to toast the beer\'s release will be held at locations throughout New England on Thursday\" March 8th March 8thHarpoon Brown Ale will be available in bottles and on draft beginning in March 2007.  An evening of celebrations to toast the beer\'s release will be held at locations throughout New England on Thursday\" March 8th including tastings at Harpoon\'s breweries in Boston including tastings at Harpoon\'s breweries in BostonHarpoon Brown Ale will be available in bottles and on draft beginning in March 2007.  An evening of celebrations to toast the beer\'s release will be held at locations throughout New England on Thursday\" March 8th including tastings at Harpoon\'s breweries in Boston MA and Windsor MA and WindsorHarpoon Brown Ale will be available in bottles and on draft beginning in March 2007.  An evening of celebrations to toast the beer\'s release will be held at locations throughout New England on Thursday\" March 8th including tastings at Harpoon\'s breweries in Boston MA and Windsor VT\" VT\"Harpoon Brown Ale will be available in bottles and on draft beginning in March 2007.  An evening of celebrations to toast the beer\'s re