(946, 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ Wit', 5, 67, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'This Belgian Ale is what you could call a wit with an attitude.  We are generous with all our ingredients - including both orange peel and coriander.  This does not stop this ale from being a good companion with seafood dishes.'),
(947, 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ Bitter', 1, 3, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'A light session ale, with an assertive hop aroma of E K Golding.  Great beer to pair with lots of different food - a good allround.'),
(948, 'Havre Stout', 1, 21, '5', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'We usually do not make compromises, but this is probably the exception.  Norwegians are dead scared of dark beers.  This is an attempt to show that there are gentle dark ales.  As such Havre Stout is smooth and drinkable.'),
(949, 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ Saison', 5, 74, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'One of our most refreshing brews, made for those hot summer days, but satisfying year \'round. Recommended serving temperature 8Â°C/45Â°F. Goes well with seafood, particularly oysters.'),
(950, 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ Amber Ale', 3, 33, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'A rather malty brew, which we think goes very well with cheeses - even well matured blue cheeses. You can also try our Amber paired with a grilled dish. Recommended serving temperature 10Â°C/50Â°F.'),
(951, 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ Imperial Brown Ale', 3, 38, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'There is a long story to this malty ale.  It was first brewed in the spring 2006 in NÃ¸rrebro Bryghus in Copenhagen, Denmark, as a joint brew between NÃ¸gne Ã˜ and NÃ¸rrebro.  NÃ¸rrebro calls their version â€œDouble Knot Brownâ€.  It is the perfect thing to drink with almost any cheese.'),
(952, 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ India Pale Ale', 3, 31, '7', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'A rich, malty, and very bitter ale. Cascade hops provide a long, fruity, and spicy after-taste.  Recommended serving temperature 10Â°C/50Â°F.  Ideal with barbequed or smoked meat dishes.'),
(953, 'NÃ¸gne Ã˜ #100', 3, 35, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Our 100th batch, brewed for the enjoyment of the brewers, but popular demand forced us to release it commercially.  This malty, yet light bodied ale has a massive hop bitterness.  Most enjoyable in a comfortable chair in front of a roaring fire.');
