(1296, 'Michelob Winter\'s Bourbon Cask Ale', 11, 141, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'During even the coldest of weather, warm up to the smooth, robust taste of our Winter\'s Bourbon Cask Ale. Full of rich aromas that you find in the winter months, hints of vanilla and flavorful hops, this is a beer that is great for pouring into a large tulip glass and enjoying with friends around a fireplace.'),
(1297, 'Tournay Black', 5, 66, '8', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_1', 'Tournay Black is a bottle conditioned, Belgian stout brewed by Brasserie de Cazeau which is a farm-brewery located in the south of Belgium.  It was originally brewed as a winter ale under the name Tournay de Noel, but later became a year-round release.  They didn\'t provide much specific detail about how it was brewed except to say that it is made with water, malts, candi-sugar, hops, and yeast.  It is 7.6% ABV with a recommended drinking temperature of +/- 50 degrees.  The brewer states that the tasting notes are of, \\roasted malts'),
(1298, 'Big A IPA', 3, 32, '10', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_3', 'Our Big A IPA has earned its share of praise over the last few years. In 2004 the New York Times named it its top IPA , and in 2007 Mens Journal Magazine included it on its list of 25 best beers in America. The last of each year\'s edition typically leaves our warehouse around mid-May, and, as always, it doesn\'t last long. Stash Wojciechowski the â€œKiller Kielbasa the â€œKiller KielbasaStash Wojciechowski the â€œKiller Kielbasaâ€ created this bonafide India Pale Ale recipe exclusively for the Smuttynose Big Beer Series.\"â€ created this bonafide India Pale Ale recipe exclusively for the Smuttynose Big Beer Series.\"Stash Wojciechowski the â€œKiller Kielbasaâ€ created this bonafide India Pale Ale recipe exclusively for the Smuttynose Big Beer Series.\"'),
