(1399, 'Pine Belt Pale Ale', 3, 26, '6', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A deep copper colored ale with a substantial malt backbone accented with British crystal malts with aggressive hop bitterness and substantial American hop flavor and aroma. The yeast profile is neutral.'),
(1400, '471 IPA', 3, 32, '9', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_0', 'Hoppy? Brother, 471 IPA redefines hoppy. 471 is a small batch, limited edition ale that was created by our Brewmaster to separate the weak from the strong. 471 is a double IPA, that combines Pale, Munich, Caramel-30, Carapils and Torrified Wheat malts, with Chinook, Centennial, Simcoe and Fuggles hops. It has a big sweet mouthfeel, followed by more hoppiness than you\'ve ever had at one time. Enjoy.'),
(1401, 'IPA Series (Simcoe)', 3, 31, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A series of single hop, small batch IPAs brewed in Camp Hill. These IPAs showcase the bitterness, flavor, and aroma of each particular hop variety.'),
(1402, 'IPA Series (Zeus)', 3, 31, '0', 'assets/img/Mockup/mockup_beer_2', 'A series of single hop, small batch IPAs brewed in Camp Hill. These IPAs showcase the bitterness, flavor, and aroma of each particular hop variety.'),
